# Error Handling And Logging Rule

- In Excalidraw async flows, wrap `loadScene()`, `saveScene()`, and `syncLoop()` in explicit `try/catch`, and handle fallback/recovery paths.
- Treat `CanvasRenderer`, `AppStateProvider`, and `Room`/`Collab` components as risky React surfaces; preserve or add `ErrorBoundary` around Canvas renderer paths and app shell boundaries.
- For scene load/save, sync, undo/redo, and network requests, report errors through existing telemetry/error-reporting (`sendTelemetryError` or `errorReporter.capture`) instead of ad-hoc logging only.
- Always attach minimum context payload: `operation`, relevant identifiers (`sceneId`, `userId`), `selectionState`, `appState` snapshot, and `stack`.
- Avoid silent failure patterns (empty `catch`, dropped promises, ignored network retries).

## How to verify

- Confirm `loadScene()`, `saveScene()`, and `syncLoop()` changes include explicit `try/catch` with recovery/propagation behavior.
- Confirm risky surfaces (`CanvasRenderer`, `AppStateProvider`, `Room`/`Collab`) are covered by an `ErrorBoundary` at the right level.
- Confirm scene/sync/undo-redo/network failures call `sendTelemetryError` or `errorReporter.capture`.
- Confirm every captured error includes `operation`, identifiers (`sceneId`/`userId`), `selectionState`, `appState` snapshot, and `stack`.
- Confirm there are no empty `catch` blocks or swallowed async errors.
